THE Central Statistical Office is considering new ways of evaluating the
harmful effects of human activities on the environment in response to a
United Nations proposal that all member states should establish integrated
economic and environmental national accounts.
In an article in the latest edition of Economic Trends, the CSO examines how
environmental statistics might be presented to clarify the interaction of
the economy and natural resources.
Environmental Issues and the National Accounts, Economic Trends, CSO, Great
George Street, London SW1P 3AQ. Pounds 2.
